Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra, this is Jimmy.

Speaker 2: How can I help you today?

Speaker 1: Hey, Jimmy, morning, man.

Speaker 2: I have a quick question for you.

Speaker 1: If I make a purchase, right, would I

Speaker 2: be put on that automatic reordering cycle?

Speaker 1: Well, we have a situation where the prescription would

Speaker 2: have you set up to have to make a purchase on the bare minimum

Speaker 1: at least twice a year.

Speaker 2: So that's like maybe like once every five months or six

Speaker 1: months or so.

Speaker 2: But that would be the minimum.

Speaker 1: But normally, to keep your prescription active,

Speaker 2: it does have to be a subscription out there.

Speaker 1: OK, but you could do it twice a year.

Speaker 2: Yeah, we can push that out for you.

Speaker 1: But normally, it would be whatever the quantity of pills

Speaker 2: you would get based off of that information.

Speaker 1: But if you make it known that you don't want it that often,

Speaker 2: we can work with you that way too as well.

Speaker 1: So that's not a problem.

Speaker 2: OK, all right, that sounds good.

Speaker 1: All right, man, yeah, I'll get back to you all then.

Speaker 2: OK, not a problem.

Speaker 1: When you do it, make sure you call us.

Speaker 2: Because if you do it online, it's

Speaker 1: going to automatically do it on a regular basis

Speaker 2: without you putting that information out there.

Speaker 1: OK?

Speaker 2: All right, I will call.

Speaker 1: Thank you, Bill.

Speaker 2: Not a problem.

Speaker 1: Take care.

Speaker 2: OK.
